  #2. Closure RC Lifecycle — the only non-deterministic lifetime

  Closures are the one type with refcounting (Closure.refcount). Every capture increments, every scope death decrements. RC cycles broken by weak self-refs in let ^rec. But closures that escape create cross-scope lifetimes.

  Dialectic questions: Could closures be arena-allocated (one arena per closure group)? Could we use epoch reclamation for closures? What if closures were immutable + structural-shared? Does the dual refcount from Exploration 5
  subsume closure RC?

  Why it matters: Closure malloc/free is the biggest remaining per-allocation overhead after bump allocation handles everything else.

